summary: i just got home and tonight was everything. i got to hold andrea’s hand and talk to her, and touched her hand once more as the...
body: i just got home and tonight was everything. i got to hold andrea’s hand and talk to her, and touched her hand once more as the show ended. and the girls next to me got rep room! i’m super happy for them since they seemed really sweet, but also leaves me just an ounce of regret and fears of “what ifs” because if only i had worn a sparlier costume or made a better poster, maybe i could too. i was literally front row on the stands and i really think tonight was my best chance to meet her, and i blew it. there’s just so many emotions inside me and after the concert ended i just felt empty, but now i’m feeling the euphoria and the sadness and regret and pure joy and comfort surrounded by people like me, celebrating someone we love so much and have been there for us for over ten years. and honestly i have no idea how the next few months or even years are going to go, because suddenly i’ve lost the thing i’ve been counting down for and hoping and praying for every single day for a year. i hope this isn’t the last time i see taylor, and one day every single one of us will get the chance to hug her somehow, or at least see her live because she is honestly a class act and talent filled with beauty and grace, and i’m incredibly grateful to have her in my life.
